        regimens. With the yoga mat in the room and 24/7 videos, guests can choose to 
        practice whenever they wish.</p>
    <br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" />
    <p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">
        After researching various schools of yoga, we short listed the Bihar School of 
        Yoga in the manner founded by Swami Satyananda. The Bihar Yoga Tradition is 
        globally renowned for its pure, simple and systematic yoga practices. It is easy 
        to learn by people at any physical, mental or spiritual level. This style has 
        also beautifully interwoven the philosophy of Karma yoga, Jnana yoga and Bhakti 
        yoga, in the intricate practices of Hatha yoga, Raja yoga and Tantra yoga. Thus 
        it truly represents the harmony of all the aspects of life.</p>
    <br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" />
